# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.1.0] - 2013-08-13
### Added
- Initial release

## [0.2.0] - 2013-08-13
### Changed
- Rewrote the entire public API

## [0.3.0] - 2013-08-13
### Added
- Support for authentication

## [0.4.0] - 2013-08-13
### Added
- Added support for getting files downloaded by torrent
- Added support for getting trackers used by a torrent
- Added support for getting peers connected to

### Changed
- The library now requires at least PHP 5.3.2
- The torrent now contains:
  * Whether it is finished
  * The up- and download rate (in bytes/s)
  * The size of the download (when completed)
  * The ETA of the download
  * The percentage of the download completed
- Made the authentication more flexible
- The client now sends an User-Agent header with each request
- Added support for starting, stopping, verifying and
  requresting a reannounce of torrents

## [0.5.0] - 2013-08-13
### Added:
- A whole lot of other stuff including management of the
  Transmission session (setting global download speed limit
  and toggling the speed limit among others).

## [0.5.2] - 2013-08-13
### Changed
- This release fixes a bug in the tests. If you are on version
  0.50 or 0.5.1 it is not necessary to update.

## [1.0.0] - 2013-10-20
- First stable release

## [2.0.0] - 2020-05-09
### Added
- `private` property in Torrent class
- `comment` property on Torrent class
- `doneDate` property on Torrent class
- `isAvailable` method on Transmission class

### Changed
- Compatibility with PHP >= 7.4
- Updated librairies in composer
